{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsswitch"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Switch is a UI element that allows to toggle between two states, typically “On” and “Off”, and used to enable or disable features, options or settings.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Switch that does not show icon or text, provides greater flexibility when creating other components that require a Switch to be displayed.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSSwitch","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also the component must be instanciated with a string parameter used as accessibility label."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is a good pratice (at least) to define a label for a component without text for accessibility reasons. This label will be vocalized by "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The vocalization tool will also use, after the label, a description of the component (if disabled, if error context), and a fake trait for switch."}]},{"level":2,"text":"Cases forbidden by design","type":"heading","anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only situation and a disabled co